out the Corleone crime family is the disturbing story of a son drawn inexorably into his father’s Mafia affairs.</p></div><span id="rank-12" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1972<!-- --> <!-- -->USA</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Francis Ford Coppola</p></a></article><article id="846a7d3b-1aee-5183-a318-903dc129dd9a" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/846a7d3b-1aee-5183-a318-903dc129dd9a/sunrise-a-song-of-two-humans"><h1>Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">11</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2021-10/sunrise-1927-george-o-brien-margaret-livingston.jpg/960x540-cropped/sunrise-1927-george-o-brien-margaret-livingston.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">The first American film by one of German expressionism’s leading exponents, this lush, atmospheric silent drama is replete with groundbreaking cinematography.</p></div><span id="rank-11" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1927<!-- --> <!-- -->USA</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->F.W. Murnau</p></a></article><article id="33de2949-3ce8-5f0b-920a-311784964aec" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/33de2949-3ce8-5f0b-920a-311784964aec/singin-in-the-rain"><h1>Singin&#x27; in the Rain</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">10</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2021-01/singin-in-the-rain-1952-gene-kelly-street-light-dancing.jpg/960x540-cropped/singin-in-the-rain-1952-gene-kelly-street-light-dancing.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">Hollywood’s troubled transition from silent to talking pictures at the end of the 1920s provided the inspiration for perhaps the greatest of movie musicals.</p></div><span id="rank-10" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1951<!-- --> <!-- -->USA</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Gene Kelly, Stanley Donen</p></a></article><article id="cacbb2df-be18-5e59-b5c3-f0eb9ea3a90d" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/cacbb2df-be18-5e59-b5c3-f0eb9ea3a90d/man-with-a-movie-camera"><h1>Man with a Movie Camera</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">9</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2021-02/man-with-a-movie-camera-1929-kino-eye.jpg/960x540-cropped/man-with-a-movie-camera-1929-kino-eye.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">Bottomless invention and frenetic, dizzying montage make this city symphony one of cinema’s sharpest, most exciting experiences nearly a century after its release.</p></div><span id="rank-9" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1929<!-- --> <!-- -->Ukrainian SSR, USSR</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Dziga Vertov</p></a></article><article id="784b550c-9db8-568a-8078-32b4957e2bbb" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/784b550c-9db8-568a-8078-32b4957e2bbb/mulholland-dr"><h1>Mulholland Dr.</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">8</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2022-03/mulholland-drive-2001-naomi-watts-laura-harring-outside-looking-up.jpg/960x540-cropped/mulholland-drive-2001-naomi-watts-laura-harring-outside-looking-up.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">Hollywood is dark and dangerous, yet alluring, in David Lynch’s acclaimed thriller.</p></div><span id="rank-8" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">2001<!-- --> <!-- -->France, USA</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->David Lynch</p></a></article><article id="bc9dc6fa-0761-553d-8324-f1fbd4bd2005" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/bc9dc6fa-0761-553d-8324-f1fbd4bd2005/beau-travail"><h1>Beau travail</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">7</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2022-11/beau-travail-1999-embrace.jpg/960x540-cropped/beau-travail-1999-embrace.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">Claire Denis’s great gift is to evoke emotion with gesture and juxtaposition. In the desert, water shimmers and ripples, naked shoulders perspire, black mosquito nets recall sheer lingerie.</p></div><span id="rank-7" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1998<!-- --> <!-- -->France</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Claire Denis</p></a></article><article id="cefccdb2-b558-5623-9c17-72b4be7bd4c1" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/cefccdb2-b558-5623-9c17-72b4be7bd4c1/2001-a-space-odyssey"><h1>2001: A Space Odyssey</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">6</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2021-11/2001-a-space-odyssey-1968-keir-dullea-helmet-red-light.jpg/960x540-cropped/2001-a-space-odyssey-1968-keir-dullea-helmet-red-light.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">Stanley Kubrick’s grand vision of mankind’s journey from its hominid beginnings to its star-child evolution is a towering achievement of science-fiction cinema.</p></div><span id="rank-6" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1968<!-- --> <!-- -->USA, United Kingdom</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Stanley Kubrick</p></a></article><article id="1b8c3bcb-842f-5ba2-90ee-39b6b40b7c21" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/1b8c3bcb-842f-5ba2-90ee-39b6b40b7c21/in-the-mood-for-love"><h1>In the Mood for Love</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">5</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2021-01/in-the-mood-for-love-2000-maggie-cheung-against-wall-with-tony-leung.jpg/960x540-cropped/in-the-mood-for-love-2000-maggie-cheung-against-wall-with-tony-leung.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">Wong Kar Wai’s masterpiece is a heartbreaking story of illicit love that pulses with the ache of repressed desire.</p></div><span id="rank-5" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">2000<!-- --> <!-- -->Hong Kong, France</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Wong Kar Wai</p></a></article><article id="65edaa59-6546-57b5-9fa3-9409f93d1383" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/65edaa59-6546-57b5-9fa3-9409f93d1383/tokyo-story"><h1>Tokyo Story</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">4</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2020-08/tokyo-story-1953-setsuko-hara-chishu-ryu.jpg/960x540-cropped/tokyo-story-1953-setsuko-hara-chishu-ryu.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">Told in Yasujirō Ozu’s simple and elegant style, this story of intergenerational discord is heartbreaking and deeply human.</p></div><span id="rank-4" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1953<!-- --> <!-- -->Japan</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Yasujirō Ozu</p></a></article><article id="f4c92833-af39-5cd6-a41e-8df5933d0dc1" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/f4c92833-af39-5cd6-a41e-8df5933d0dc1/citizen-kane"><h1>Citizen Kane</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">3</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2022-11/citizen-kane-1941-orson-welles-political-podium.jpg/960x540-cropped/citizen-kane-1941-orson-welles-political-podium.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">Famously sitting at the top of the Sight and Sound Greatest Films of All Time poll from 1962 to 2002, Orson Welles’s debut, about newspaper magnate Charles Foster Kane, remains an enduring classic.</p></div><span id="rank-3" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1941<!-- --> <!-- -->USA</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Orson Welles</p></a></article><article id="489eada8-7d7e-594c-acac-5903f43f4b85" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/489eada8-7d7e-594c-acac-5903f43f4b85/vertigo"><h1>Vertigo</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">2</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2021-03/vertigo-1958-012-madeleine-bouquet_1000x750.jpg/960x540-cropped/vertigo-1958-012-madeleine-bouquet_1000x750.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">A former detective with a fear of heights is hired to follow a woman apparently possessed by the past, in Alfred Hitchcock’s timeless thriller about obsession.</p></div><span id="rank-2" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1958<!-- --> <!-- -->USA</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Alfred Hitchcock</p></a></article><article id="00638537-48d0-5522-9502-4e5ba0166194" class="PreviewCard__Article-sc-7y1ad6-0 gUNVnM"><a href="/film/00638537-48d0-5522-9502-4e5ba0166194/jeanne-dielman-23-quai-du-commerce-1080-bruxelles"><h1>Jeanne Dielman, 23 Quai du Commerce, 1080 Bruxelles</h1><div class="PreviewCard__image"><p class="ResultsPage__Rank-sc-of10co-1 gsVRkZ PreviewCard__label">1</p><img src="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2022-11/jeanne-dielman-23-commerce-quay-1080-brussels-1975-delphine-seyrig-reflection.jpg/960x540-cropped/jeanne-dielman-23-commerce-quay-1080-brussels-1975-delphine-seyrig-reflection.jpg" alt="" loading="lazy"/><p class="PreviewCard__description">A magnificent epic of experimental cinema offering a feminist perspective on recurrent events of everyday life.</p></div><span id="rank-1" class="ResultsPage__Span-sc-of10co-3 kvXPxe"></span><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">1975<!-- --> <!-- -->Belgium, France</p><p class="ResultsPage__P-sc-of10co-2 eUEyPc">Directed by <!-- -->Chantal Akerman</p></a></article></div><div><div class="ResultsPage__BannerWrapper-sc-of10co-5 fbKcWM reversed"><img src="/dist/server/73c183e85ebe0f9f8f95abff27337bbb.jpg" alt="Image of Jeanne Dielman" class="ResultsPage__CoverImage-sc-of10co-6 bbwBoC"/><div class="ResultsPage__PromoWrapper-sc-of10co-7 dNYQja"><img src="/dist/server/6b35d8d0dfc135ee1de3f19ac41e07c0.png" alt="BFI Player logo"/><h2 class="ResultsPage__H2-sc-of10co-8 ldKTBE">Stream the Greatest Films of All Time</h2><p class="ResultsPage__Description-sc-of10co-15 cpbJJI">Discover a selection of hand-picked highlights available to watch at home.</p><a href="https://player.bfi.org.uk/sight-and-sound-poll?utm_source=bfi.org.uk&amp;utm_medium=banner&amp;utm_campaign=sight_and_sound_greatest_films_2022" title="Explore now" class